Source: chip-desktop-configs
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ben Young <computermouth@proton.me>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9)
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: github.com/NextThingCo

Package: chip-desktop-configs
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, chip-configs
Description: Shared openbox/desktop look-and-feel for the C.H.I.P.
 GTK theme + small-screen tweaks, a compact tint2 panel, and an openbox autostart
 that launches it. Flavor-agnostic desktop shell config; the openbox/tint2 bits
 are inert under other WMs (e.g. pocketchip's awesome). Depends on chip-configs
 for the underlying hardware setup.
